---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div
    class="max-w-[38rem] w-full text-sm [&_a]:text-xs [&_a]:text-[#909090]"
  >
    <nav class="mb-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-[#909090]">‚Üê back to home</a>
    </nav>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-normal mb-4">
        calculadora de isr - occ mundial<span class="caret">_</span>
      </h1>

      <div class="mb-10">
        <Image
          src="https://placehold.co/800x400"
          alt="Vercel redesign full preview"
          width={800}
          height={400}
          class="rounded-md"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-sm [&>p]:text-[#909090] [&>p]:text-xs">
        <h2 class="font-normal text-white">project overview</h2>
        <p>
          the vercel.com redesign project aimed to refresh and modernize the
          online presence of vercel, a cloud platform for static sites and
          serverless functions. the goal was to create a sleek, performant, and
          user-friendly website that reflects vercel's cutting-edge technology
          and commitment to developer experience.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-normal text-white">key features</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-[#909090]">
          <li>responsive design optimized for all device sizes</li>
          <li>improved navigation and information architecture</li>
          <li>
            enhanced visual hierarchy to highlight key products and features
          </li>
          <li>integration of interactive demos and code snippets</li>
          <li>optimized performance with next.js and vercel's edge network</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-normal text-white">technologies used</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-[#909090]">
          <li>next.js for server-side rendering and static site generation</li>
          <li>react for building user interface components</li>
          <li>typescript for type-safe javascript development</li>
          <li>tailwind css for rapid and responsive styling</li>
          <li>framer motion for smooth animations and transitions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-normal text-white">challenges and solutions</h2>
        <p>
          one of the main challenges was balancing the need for a content-rich
          site with fast load times. we implemented advanced code-splitting
          techniques and leveraged next.js's image optimization to ensure
          optimal performance without sacrificing visual appeal or
          functionality.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-normal text-white">results</h2>
        <p>
          the redesigned vercel.com saw a 30% increase in user engagement and a
          25% reduction in bounce rate. the new design also contributed to a 20%
          increase in sign-ups for vercel's services within the first month of
          launch.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-normal text-white">learnings</h2>
        <p>
          this project reinforced the importance of a user-centered design
          approach and the value of iterative development. it also showcased the
          power of next.js and vercel's platform in creating high-performance
          web applications.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
